## Property Mapping Deep Dive

Property mappers ensure bidirectional synchronization:

```csharp
public class EntryHandler : ViewHandler<IEntry, SkiaEntry>
{
    private static void MapText(EntryHandler handler, IEntry entry)
    {
        handler.PlatformView.Text = entry.Text;
    }

    private static void MapTextColor(EntryHandler handler, IEntry entry)
    {
        handler.PlatformView.TextColor = entry.TextColor.ToSKColor();
    }

    private static void MapPlaceholder(EntryHandler handler, IEntry entry)
    {
        handler.PlatformView.Placeholder = entry.Placeholder;
    }

    protected override void ConnectHandler(SkiaEntry platformView)
    {
        base.ConnectHandler(platformView);

        // Wire up events from platform view to virtual view
        platformView.TextChanged += OnTextChanged;
        platformView.Completed += OnCompleted;
    }

    private void OnTextChanged(object? sender, TextChangedEventArgs e)
    {
        if (VirtualView != null)
        {
            VirtualView.Text = e.NewTextValue;
        }
    }
}
```

## Type Conversion Utilities

OpenMaui provides seamless conversion between MAUI and Skia types:

```csharp
public static class ColorExtensions
{
    public static SKColor ToSKColor(this Color color)
    {
        return new SKColor(
            (byte)(color.Red * 255),
            (byte)(color.Green * 255),
            (byte)(color.Blue * 255),
            (byte)(color.Alpha * 255)
        );
    }
}

public static class RectExtensions
{
    public static SKRect ToSKRect(this Rect rect)
    {
        return new SKRect(
            (float)rect.Left,
            (float)rect.Top,
            (float)rect.Right,
            (float)rect.Bottom
        );
    }
}
```

These extensions ensure that developers work with familiar MAUI types (`Color`, `Rect`, `Size`, `Thickness`) while OpenMaui handles the Skia conversion internally.

## Native Service Integration

Handlers also bridge to native Linux services:

```csharp
public class FilePickerHandler
{
    public async Task<FileResult?> PickAsync(PickOptions? options)
    {
        // Try xdg-desktop-portal first (Flatpak, Snap compatible)
        if (IsPortalAvailable())
        {
            return await PickViaPortal(options);
        }

        // Fall back to native dialogs
        if (IsKDE())
        {
            return await PickViaKDialog(options);
        }
        else
        {
            return await PickViaZenity(options);
        }
    }
}
```

This ensures that file pickers, notifications, and other system services feel native to each desktop environment (GNOME, KDE, XFCE).

## Custom Control Example

Developers can create custom controls using the same pattern:

```csharp
// 1. Define the interface
public interface ICustomGauge : IView
{
    double Value { get; }
    double Minimum { get; }
    double Maximum { get; }
    Color GaugeColor { get; }
}

// 2. Create the Skia view
public class SkiaCustomGauge : SkiaView
{
    public double Value { get; set; }
    public double Minimum { get; set; }
    public double Maximum { get; set; }
    public SKColor GaugeColor { get; set; }

    public override void Draw(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect dirtyRect)
    {
        var paint = new SKPaint
        {
            Color = GaugeColor,
            Style = SKPaintStyle.Stroke,
            StrokeWidth = 10,
            IsAntialias = true
        };

        var angle = (Value - Minimum) / (Maximum - Minimum) * 270;
        canvas.DrawArc(_bounds, -225, (float)angle, false, paint);
    }
}

// 3. Create the handler
public class CustomGaugeHandler : ViewHandler<ICustomGauge, SkiaCustomGauge>
{
    public static IPropertyMapper<ICustomGauge, CustomGaugeHandler> Mapper =
        new PropertyMapper<ICustomGauge, CustomGaugeHandler>()
        {
            [nameof(ICustomGauge.Value)] = MapValue,
            [nameof(ICustomGauge.GaugeColor)] = MapGaugeColor,
        };

    protected override SkiaCustomGauge CreatePlatformView()
    {
        return new SkiaCustomGauge();
    }
}

// 4. Register the handler
builder.ConfigureMauiHandlers(handlers =>
{
    handlers.AddHandler<ICustomGauge, CustomGaugeHandler>();
});
```

This architecture provides complete flexibility while maintaining MAUI's cross-platform abstractions.

## Render Caching Strategies

Rendering complex UI elements every frame is expensive. OpenMaui employs sophisticated **caching strategies** to minimize redundant drawing operations, dramatically improving performance for static or infrequently changing content.

## SKPicture-Based Caching

Skia's `SKPicture` provides a recording mechanism for draw commands:

```csharp
public abstract class SkiaView
{
    private SKPicture? _cachedPicture;
    private bool _cacheDirty = true;

    public bool EnableRenderCaching { get; set; } = false;

    public override void Draw(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect dirtyRect)
    {
        if (EnableRenderCaching)
        {
            if (_cacheDirty || _cachedPicture == null)
            {
                // Record drawing commands
                using var recorder = new SKPictureRecorder();
                var recordingCanvas = recorder.BeginRecording(_bounds);

                DrawContent(recordingCanvas, dirtyRect);

                _cachedPicture?.Dispose();
                _cachedPicture = recorder.EndRecording();
                _cacheDirty = false;
            }

            // Replay cached commands
            canvas.DrawPicture(_cachedPicture);
        }
        else
        {
            // Direct rendering
            DrawContent(canvas, dirtyRect);
        }
    }

    protected abstract void DrawContent(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect dirtyRect);

    public override void Invalidate()
    {
        _cacheDirty = true;
        base.Invalidate();
    }
}
```

## Image Caching System

The `SkiaImage` control implements multi-level caching:

```csharp
public class SkiaImage : SkiaView
{
    private static readonly Dictionary<string, SKBitmap> _imageCache = new();
    private static readonly object _cacheLock = new();

    private SKBitmap? _bitmap;
    private string? _source;

    public ImageSource Source
    {
        get => _source;
        set
        {
            if (_source != value)
            {
                _source = value;
                LoadImageAsync(value);
            }
        }
    }

    private async Task LoadImageAsync(ImageSource source)
    {
        if (source is FileImageSource fileSource)
        {
            var path = fileSource.File;

            // Check memory cache first
            lock (_cacheLock)
            {
                if (_imageCache.TryGetValue(path, out var cached))
                {
                    _bitmap = cached;
                    Invalidate();
                    return;
                }
            }

            // Load from disk
            _bitmap = await Task.Run(() => SKBitmap.Decode(path));

            // Cache for future use
            lock (_cacheLock)
            {
                _imageCache[path] = _bitmap;
            }

            Invalidate();
        }
        else if (source is StreamImageSource streamSource)
        {
            var stream = await streamSource.Stream(CancellationToken.None);
            _bitmap = SKBitmap.Decode(stream);
            Invalidate();
        }
    }

    public override void Draw(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect dirtyRect)
    {
        if (_bitmap != null)
        {
            canvas.DrawBitmap(_bitmap, _bounds);
        }
    }
}
```

## SVG Caching with Svg.Skia

SVG rendering is expensive, so OpenMaui caches rasterized versions:

```csharp
public class SkiaSvgImage : SkiaImage
{
    private SKPicture? _svgPicture;
    private SKBitmap? _rasterizedCache;
    private Size _lastRenderSize;

    private void LoadSvg(string path)
    {
        var svg = new SKSvg();
        _svgPicture = svg.Load(path);
    }

    public override void Draw(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect dirtyRect)
    {
        if (_svgPicture == null)
            return;

        var currentSize = new Size(_bounds.Width, _bounds.Height);

        // Re-rasterize if size changed
        if (_rasterizedCache == null || _lastRenderSize != currentSize)
        {
            _rasterizedCache?.Dispose();

            var info = new SKImageInfo(
                (int)_bounds.Width,
                (int)_bounds.Height,
                SKColorType.Rgba8888,
                SKAlphaType.Premul
            );

            _rasterizedCache = new SKBitmap(info);

            using var cacheCanvas = new SKCanvas(_rasterizedCache);
            cacheCanvas.Clear(SKColors.Transparent);
            cacheCanvas.DrawPicture(_svgPicture);

            _lastRenderSize = currentSize;
        }

        canvas.DrawBitmap(_rasterizedCache, _bounds);
    }
}
```

## Text Layout Caching

Text shaping with HarfBuzz is computationally expensive, especially for complex scripts:

```csharp
public class SkiaLabel : SkiaView
{
    private string? _text;
    private SKFont? _font;
    private SKTextBlob? _cachedTextBlob;
    private bool _textLayoutDirty = true;

    public string Text
    {
        get => _text;
        set
        {
            if (_text != value)
            {
                _text = value;
                _textLayoutDirty = true;
                Invalidate();
            }
        }
    }

    public override void Draw(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect dirtyRect)
    {
        if (_textLayoutDirty || _cachedTextBlob == null)
        {
            // Shape text using HarfBuzz
            var shaper = new SKShaper(_font.Typeface);
            _cachedTextBlob = shaper.Shape(_text, _font);
            _textLayoutDirty = false;
        }

        var paint = new SKPaint
        {
            Color = TextColor,
            IsAntialias = true
        };

        canvas.DrawText(_cachedTextBlob, _bounds.Left, _bounds.Top, paint);
    }
}
```

## Collection View Virtualization

The `SkiaCollectionView` implements virtualization to cache only visible items:

```csharp
public class SkiaCollectionView : SkiaView
{
    private readonly Dictionary<int, SkiaView> _visibleItemCache = new();
    private readonly HashSet<int> _currentlyVisible = new();

    public override void Draw(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect dirtyRect)
    {
        var visibleRange = CalculateVisibleRange(_scrollOffset, _bounds.Height);
        _currentlyVisible.Clear();

        for (int i = visibleRange.Start; i < visibleRange.End; i++)
        {
            _currentlyVisible.Add(i);

            if (!_visibleItemCache.TryGetValue(i, out var itemView))
            {
                // Create and cache new item view
                itemView = CreateItemView(i);
                _visibleItemCache[i] = itemView;
            }

            var itemBounds = CalculateItemBounds(i);
            itemView.Arrange(itemBounds);
            itemView.Draw(canvas, dirtyRect);
        }

        // Cleanup items that scrolled out of view
        var itemsToRemove = _visibleItemCache.Keys
            .Where(k => !_currentlyVisible.Contains(k))
            .ToList();

        foreach (var key in itemsToRemove)
        {
            _visibleItemCache[key].Dispose();
            _visibleItemCache.Remove(key);
        }
    }
}
```

## Cache Invalidation Strategy

Proper cache invalidation is critical:

```csharp
public abstract class SkiaView
{
    protected void InvalidateCache(CacheLevel level)
    {
        switch (level)
        {
            case CacheLevel.Paint:
                // Only visual properties changed
                _cacheDirty = true;
                Invalidate();
                break;

            case CacheLevel.Layout:
                // Size/position changed, invalidate layout cache
                _layoutCache = null;
                _cacheDirty = true;
                InvalidateLayout();
                break;

            case CacheLevel.Deep:
                // Structure changed, invalidate entire subtree
                InvalidateDescendants();
                _cacheDirty = true;
                InvalidateLayout();
                break;
        }
    }
}

public enum CacheLevel
{
    Paint,    // Color, stroke, etc.
    Layout,   // Size, position
    Deep      // Children added/removed
}
```

## Memory Management

OpenMaui includes cache size limits to prevent memory exhaustion:

```csharp
public class ImageCacheManager
{
    private const long MaxCacheSizeBytes = 100 * 1024 * 1024; // 100 MB
    private long _currentCacheSize = 0;

    public void AddToCache(string key, SKBitmap bitmap)
    {
        var bitmapSize = bitmap.ByteCount;

        // Evict old items if necessary
        while (_currentCacheSize + bitmapSize > MaxCacheSizeBytes)
        {
            EvictLeastRecentlyUsed();
        }

        _imageCache[key] = bitmap;
        _currentCacheSize += bitmapSize;
    }

    private void EvictLeastRecentlyUsed()
    {
        // LRU eviction logic
    }
}
```

These caching strategies ensure that OpenMaui remains performant even with complex UIs containing hundreds of controls and images.

