## Render Clipping

The rendering engine uses dirty regions to set canvas clip rects:

```csharp
public void RenderFrame(SKCanvas canvas)
{
    var dirtyRegions = _dirtyRegionTracker.GetDirtyRegions();

    if (dirtyRegions.Count == 0)
        return; // Nothing to draw

    foreach (var dirtyRect in dirtyRegions)
    {
        canvas.Save();
        canvas.ClipRect(dirtyRect);

        // Only views intersecting this rect will draw
        RenderViewHierarchy(canvas, dirtyRect);

        canvas.Restore();
    }
}

private void RenderViewHierarchy(SKCanvas canvas, SKRect clipRect)
{
    foreach (var view in _rootViews)
    {
        if (view.Bounds.IntersectsWith(clipRect))
        {
            view.Draw(canvas, clipRect);
        }
    }
}
```

## Layout Invalidation vs. Paint Invalidation

OpenMaui distinguishes between layout changes (requiring measurement) and paint changes:

```csharp
public abstract class SkiaLayoutView : SkiaView
{
    private bool _needsLayout;

    public void InvalidateLayout()
    {
        _needsLayout = true;

        // Layout changes affect entire subtree
        foreach (var child in Children)
        {
            child.InvalidateLayout();
        }

        // Trigger measurement and arrangement
        RequestLayout();
    }

    protected override void OnBeforeDraw()
    {
        if (_needsLayout)
        {
            Measure(_constraints.Width, _constraints.Height);
            Arrange(_bounds);
            _needsLayout = false;
        }
    }
}
